Directions
Preheat oven to 350°F. Lightly oil a 9- by-5-inch loaf pan.
In a large bowl, whisk together the whole wheat flour, almond flour,
oats, flaxseed, cinnamon, baking powder, baking soda, and salt.
In a medium bowl, mash bananas very well with a fork. Add in melted
coconut oil, maple syrup, applesauce, vanilla, and lemon juice.
Alternatively, blend bananas and wet ingredients together in a food
processor for a smoother result. Pour the wet ingredients into the dry
ingredients and mix gently. Gently stir in nuts and chocolate chips. Be
careful not to overmix as you will create a tough, not tender, bread.
Pour the batter into prepared pan and bake for 50 to 55 minutes.
You’ll start to really smell the bread when it is close to being done.
Bread is done when the edges are nicely browned, the bread is just
firm to the touch, and a toothpick or knife inserted into the middle
comes out clean. Cool for about 20 minutes. Insert a knife along the
edge of the pan and invert onto a cutting board or plate. Let cool
another 10 minutes before cutting, or gently slice while warm.
