Chef Linda: Working as a chef at Catskill Animal Sanctuary can often feel like an episode of
Dinner: Impossible. Whether we’re feeding five hundred people on a scorching summer day or
catering an upscale vegan cocktail party—in a barn, without a kitchen—we are always up for the
challenge! Hearts swelled and tongues wagged when we served our deviled potatoes at a cocktail
party for our beloved animal sponsors. Using common ingredients like potatoes and chickpeas to
create a familiar party staple assured folks that we can make food we love while respecting all
beings. With such simple changes, you’ll find how liberating living egg-free can be.
