¾ cup walnuts, finely chopped (or raw pumpkin or sunflower seeds)
½ cup breadcrumbs, regular or gluten-free
1 Tbsp nutritional yeast (optional)
1 tsp dried oregano
1 tsp dried thyme
Directions
1.
2.
3.
Preheat oven to 375°F. Wipe dirt from mushrooms, remove stems,
finely chop, and set aside. Place mushroom caps in a large bowl.
Drizzle with 2 tablespoons of oil and sprinkle with ½ teaspoon of salt.
Toss to coat and arrange stem-side down in a casserole dish. Bake for
10 to 12 minutes until mushrooms have released their moisture and
turned dark brown.
While the mushrooms are baking, heat the remaining 1 tablespoon of
oil in a large pan. Add the chopped mushroom stems, garlic, and
remaining ½ teaspoon of salt. Cook, stirring occasionally, for 5 to 8
