Directions
To make the Cajun seasoning, mix all the ingredients together in a jar
or zip-top plastic bag.
To make the gumbo, heat 2 tablespoons of oil in a large, heavybottomed pot over medium heat. Add mushrooms and salt. Cook,
stirring occasionally, for 8 to 10 minutes, or until mushrooms have
browned and released their liquid. Transfer mushrooms to a bowl and
set aside.
Heat remaining 3 tablespoons of oil in the same pot over low heat.
Whisk in flour. Cook, stirring continually for about 5 minutes. It’s
important to stir continually and not allow the mixture to stick to the
bottom and burn.
When the flour has turn a golden-dark brown, add onion, celery, bell
peppers, and garlic. Cook for about 10 minutes, or until vegetables
have softened. Add the Cajun seasoning, vegetable broth, zucchini,
pecans, and cooked mushrooms.
Let the stew come to a simmer, stirring occasionally, until zucchini is
tender, about 15 minutes. Stir in lemon juice. Taste and adjust
seasonings if desired. To serve, spoon rice into the bottom of deep
bowls and ladle the gumbo on top. Garnish with scallions.
