until it darkens slightly. Add onions, peppers, garlic, paprika, salt,
coriander, and crushed red pepper flakes. Cover and cook until onions
and peppers have softened slightly, about 8 minutes. Add tomatoes,
hearts of palm, tofu, potatoes, vegetable broth, and coconut milk.
Simmer for 25 to 30 minutes, until all the vegetables have softened
and potatoes can be pierced with a fork. Stir in lime juice and
plantains.
