magical experience. Garam refers to the intensity and heat of the spices, though it doesn’t necessarily
mean spicy, and masala is a term used for a mixture of spices. Served over rice or your favorite
cooked whole grain, this humble dish is surprisingly addictive. In our Compassionate Cuisine Indian
food class, we add a generous dollop of Cashew Sour Cream (pg. 188) to add a creamy, satisfying
finish.
