Chef Linda: Is there anything that cauliflower can’t do? This healthy cruciferous vegetable has
worked its way onto the main stage and can be enjoyed as a plant-based alternative to steak, puréed
to make cream sauces, or roasted with hot sauce to make vegan Buffalo Cauliflower Bites (pg. 45).
Cauliflower can also serve as a lower-carb substitute for rice. All you need is a food grater or food
processor to turn a head of cauliflower into a heaping bowl of “rice.” In this recipe, you’ll get the
comforting texture and “south of the border” flavors without overdoing the carbs on your plate.
