Chef Linda: Nothing says summer like the flavors of BBQ. Smoky, tangy, sweet, or hot, there’s
good reason to love anything slathered in BBQ sauce, especially when it’s healthy and
compassionate. Why settle for a store-bought bottle of sauce when you can make your own? Made
mostly with pantry ingredients, this BBQ sauce has a distinct, clean flavor, made with less sugar than
most store-bought versions and no preservatives. You’ll also enjoy the freedom to adjust the flavors
to suit your taste. Tempeh is a wonderful canvas for this sassy sauce and stands up mightily to your
favorite buns and vegan coleslaw—but cauliflower, tofu, or portobello work just as well.
