Chef Linda: This recipe was developed for an Italian cooking class at the Sanctuary and uses
artichoke hearts, cannellini beans, and cashews to create a thick, creamy, and compassionate
alternative to traditional alfredo sauce. It comes together easily in a blender and would be just fine
tossed with your favorite pasta, but we encourage you to make the tomatoes and shiitake crisps to get
the full effect of the complementary flavors, colors, and textures. The tangy pan-roasted tomatoes
burst in your mouth, while shiitake crisps deliver a salty, smoky, crunchy finish. We’ll warn you:
