To make shiitake crisps, preheat oven to 375°F. Line a baking tray
with parchment paper. Place shiitake slices in a mound on the baking
tray and drizzle with oil. Toss to coat with oil. Arrange in a single
layer and sprinkle with salt and paprika. Roast for about 25 minutes,
