Chef Linda: Sofrito, used in so many dishes with Cuban, Puerto Rican, or Spanish influence, is that
special something you can’t quite put your finger on. It’s a unique flavor that turns a boring dish of
rice and beans into a lively affair. Flavorful and sometimes spicy, this sauce typically consists of
onions, garlic, peppers, and tomatoes, depending on what part of the world your recipe originates. In
this recipe, the sauce is used to braise spiced tofu and beans, creating a complex and delicious
combination. A dollop of cool, creamy Cashew Sour Cream (pg. 188) provides the perfect balance.
