Chef Linda: When the weather turns chilly and comfort food is top of mind, you’ll turn to this recipe
again and again. Traditionally, shepherd’s pie is made with ground beef or lamb. We developed this
dish for a Sanctuary cooking class on comfort food to demonstrate how using a kinder approach can
still yield familiar tastes and textures. Lentils and mushrooms provide the rich, meaty flavor. You’ll
also find the other ingredients comfortably reassuring: potatoes, carrots, onions, celery, and peas. We
love the ease of making and baking this dish in a cast iron skillet, but use a 9-inch square casserole
