Chef Linda: We’re in love with the combination of textures and flavors that create this earthy,
wholesome dish. Celery root, or celeriac, is knobby and gnarly on the outside, but once peeled, you’ll
find its grassy, delicate celery flavor delightful in recipes like this one. Try it in cool-weather soups
and stews as an alternative to potatoes. If you can’t find celery root, parsnips make a fine substitute,
as do carrots—just watch the cooking time and adjust to ensure proper doneness. Fennel adds a
delicate sweet note here—whether sautéed, roasted, or raw, get to know this versatile vegetable, and
you’ll add interest to everyday dishes.
