To Serve
Coconut Whipped Cream (pg. 223)
Directions
To make the crust, add the pecans, chocolate chips, and salt to a food
processor and pulse until mixture is ground but still retains some
medium chunks of chips and nuts. Drain the dates, squeezing out
excess water, and add to the food processor. Pulse until everything is
combined. Empty mixture into a 9-inch pie plate and press firmly up
the sides and on the bottom. Finish by pressing firmly all the way
around using the bottom of a metal measuring cup. Wash the food
