Chef Linda: Spiced just right with aromatic cinnamon, ginger, and cloves, this pie is a healthy
alternative to most holiday desserts and the only pumpkin pie recipe you’ll ever need. The crust is a
simple and nourishing blend of dried fruit and nuts, perfect for everyone, including your gluten-free
guests. Without eggs, cornstarch is all you need to thicken the filling. A few minutes on the stovetop
activates the starch and makes for a rich pie after it is chilled. We demonstrated this pie at our annual
Thanksgiving event, and even the confirmed pumpkin-pie-haters asked for the recipe. With every
bite, this pie will inspire compassionate eating at your holiday table.
